# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# EASIEST SETUP — bundled server + Personal Access Token (no Azure admin needed)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. Create a PAT (takes 2 minutes, any DevOps user can):
#      dev.azure.com → click your avatar → ... "User settings" →
#      Personal access tokens → New Token
#      Scopes: "Work Items (Read)" + "Code (Read)"  (or Full access if unsure)
# 2. Pick an access code your users will type to sign in.
# 3. npm run build && npm start   → http://localhost:3001
ADO_PAT=
APP_ACCESS_CODE=
# PORT=3001
# For Azure DevOps Server (on-prem), point at your collection URL:
# ADO_BASE_URL=https://dev.azure.com

# ── Azure DevOps wiki source (used by both server and Entra modes) ──────────
ADO_ORG=mamsoftglobal
ADO_PROJECT=vast-online
ADO_WIKI=vast-online.wiki
ADO_ROOT_PATH=/Vast Online Core

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OPTIONAL — Microsoft Entra ID sign-in (needs an app registration by an admin)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# LEAVE THESE EMPTY unless an admin has created the app registration — the
# client ID must be the registration's GUID. (Invalid values are ignored.)
# When set, the app skips the bundled server and users sign in with their own
# Microsoft accounts; Azure DevOps permissions then apply per user.
#   1. Azure Portal → Microsoft Entra ID → App registrations → New (SPA platform,
#      redirect URIs: http://localhost:5173 + production URL)
#   2. API permissions → Azure DevOps → Delegated → user_impersonation → grant consent
VITE_ENTRA_CLIENT_ID=
VITE_ENTRA_TENANT_ID=

# Frontend copies of the wiki source (Entra mode calls Azure DevOps directly)
VITE_ADO_ORG=mamsoftglobal
VITE_ADO_PROJECT=vast-online
VITE_ADO_WIKI=vast-online.wiki
VITE_ADO_ROOT_PATH=/Vast Online Core
